<LEADPARA>  CHRISTOPHER COLUMBUS, and the 90 men who sailed the three ships under his
command, set out on their famous voyage 499 years ago this weekend, Aug. 3,
1492.;    We know many things about Columbus and his "discovery" of the New
World. We know, for example, that he had red hair, blue eyes and was at least
6 feet tall (almost a giant by the standards of his day). We don't know much
more about his appearance because not a single portrait was ever painted of
him during his life.  </LEADPARA>
