<LEADPARA>  THE quincentenary of Christopher Columbus' first voyage to the New World will
be celebrated all over the world. Among the planned events:;    (check) EXPO
'92 -- Seville, Spain, April 20 to Oct. 12, 1992. The theme is "The Age of
Discovery," and the spirit of Columbus will be very much in evidence. The fair
will take place on an island in the Guadalquivir River, opposite the old part
of the city. The island is being fitted with pavilions, parks, theaters,
sports arenas and a hotel complex, and a monastery in which Columbus lived for
eight years is being renovated.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Travel  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  COLUMBUS CALENDAR  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Cover Story
See also related stories on P. 1T, 7T, 8T, 9T and 10T of this section
The Great Columbus Chase  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     (check) <LOCATION>COLOMBO</LOCATION> '92 -- <LOCATION>Genoa</LOCATION>, <DATE>May 15-Aug</DATE>. 15. Another Expo, this one
concentrating on maritime activities and on <LOCATION>Columbus</LOCATION> himself.;    (check)
GRAND REGATTA <LOCATION>COLUMBUS</LOCATION> '92 -- <LOCATION>Puerto Rico</LOCATION>, <DATE>May-June 1992</DATE>. A fleet of tall
sailing ships and hundreds of pleasure craft will sail from <LOCATION>Cadiz</LOCATION> and arrive
at <LOCATION>San Juan</LOCATION> in <DATE>May 1992</DATE>. There will be events in <LOCATION>San Juan June 10-14.</LOCATION>;   
(check) <DATE>1992</DATE> SUMMER OLYMPICS -- <LOCATION>Barcelona</LOCATION>, <DATE>July 25-Aug</DATE>. 9, <DATE>1992</DATE>. The games are
dedicated to Columbus.;    (check) CIRCA 1492: Art in the Age of Exploration
-- <ORGANIZATION>National Gallery</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>Washington</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>D.C.</LOCATION>, <DATE>Oct. 12, 1991</DATE> through <DATE>Jan. 12, 1992</DATE>. It
will include more than 400 paintings, sculptures, drawings, maps, screens,
scrolls, scientific instruments and other objects from the period of his
lifetime, borrowed from about 20 countries.;    (check) AmeriFlora '92 --
Beginning <DATE>April 3, 1992</DATE>, <LOCATION>Columbus</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Ohio</LOCATION>. The 17-day, indoor <ORGANIZATION>Grand
International Floral Exposition</ORGANIZATION> is an international garden festival being held
as part of the 500th anniversary celebrations. The city thought about a
world's fair, but decided to go with a huge flower show instead.;    (check)
"YEAR OF DISCOVERY" -- Beginning <DATE>Oct. 12, 1991</DATE>, throughout <LOCATION>South Carolina</LOCATION>.
Among the programs scheduled are the "Discovery Photo Album" modeled after the
photo book "A Day in the Life of the <LOCATION>United States</LOCATION>." Citizens will be asked to
take pictures of unusual or historic things in their county <DATE>Oct. 12, 1991</DATE>. The
photos will be used to create a state photo album.  </TEXT>
