<LEADPARA>  QUESTION: Mr. Columbus, how do you feel about the 500-year-celebration of your
discovery of America?;    ANSWER: My God, has it been that long? 500 years? I
haven't been back there. I bet the place has changed.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  SORRY, CHRIS, BUT THE NEW WORLD IS THE SAME
OLD RIP-OFF  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  At Large  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Q: Yes, it has, <PERSON>Mr. Columbus</PERSON>. You wouldn't recognize it.;    A: Well, I bet
they have a lot more Indians. Those people were everywhere.;    Q: We call
them Native Americans now, <PERSON>Mr. Columbus</PERSON>. And they are virtually nowhere. They
were mostly killed by the white men.;    A: What are you talking! What is this
American stuff? I was sailing to India.;    Q: No, <PERSON>Mr. Columbus</PERSON>, that was
<LOCATION>America</LOCATION>. We call this part of it the <LOCATION>United States of America</LOCATION> now.;    A: The
world has gone wacky. If it wasn't <LOCATION>India</LOCATION>, why didn't they call it
Columbusland? I discovered it.;    Q: Well, they named it after <PERSON>Amerigo
Vespucci</PERSON>. He was an Italian. They do have a city called <LOCATION>Columbus</LOCATION> in <LOCATION>Ohio.</LOCATION>;   
A: <PERSON>Vespucci</PERSON>. They named it after him? That Mafioso! And where is <LOCATION>Ohio</LOCATION>? Did I
discover it?;    Q: No, <PERSON>Mr. Columbus</PERSON>. It was discovered by early Native
Americans.;    A: Again with the Native Americans. I tell you, I can recognize
an Indian at 5,000 feet! Why did you change the name?;    Q: It was
politically correct.;    A: What? What kind of word is that? My New World
sounds all messed up.;    Q: Well, it has changed. A lot of people claim now
that you were no hero. That you were a tyrant who cut off the natives' hands.;
   A: So?;    Q: You admit it?;    A: I'm not sure. You sound sneaky. What
does <PERSON>Queen Isabella</PERSON> say?;    Q: She's dead.;    A: Good. She brought me home
in chains. You want to talk meanness, you should mention that. And she had
promised me a few nice acres for a home in <LOCATION>Florida</LOCATION>. I bet <LOCATION>Florida</LOCATION> has
changed.;    Q: It's very crowded. Very hard to find a few nice acres in
<LOCATION>Florida</LOCATION>. Did you have any special dreams for your New World?;    A: Of course.
I wanted to open a chain of <ORGANIZATION>Columbus Pizza Shops</ORGANIZATION>. They didn't know what pizza
was when I landed. The Indians would have loved it. You can't beat Italian
food.;    Q: There are lots of pizza shops in America.;    A: The West
Indies!;    Q: There, too.;    A: Well, I was a man ahead of my time. I could
have used the <LOCATION>Pinta</LOCATION> and the <LOCATION>Santa Maria</LOCATION> for cruises, you know, for tourists.
Could have charged 20, 30 lire a trip.;    Q: You could get thousands of
dollars now. And millions of lire.;    A: Ahead of my time. Tell me, did they
ever discover <LOCATION>California</LOCATION>?;    Q: You know about that?;    A: Of course. It was
my secret. I was going to build a huge amusement park there.;    Q: Amazing!
There is a huge amusement park there! Disneyland. And there's <ORGANIZATION>Disney World</ORGANIZATION> in
<LOCATION>Florida</LOCATION>!;    A: On my acres, I bet! Selling pizza all over the place! I was
badly treated. The New World is a rip-off joint!;    Q: Well, if it is, lots
of people think you started it. By your greed and cruelty.;    A: MY greed?
They don't call it <LOCATION>Columbusland</LOCATION>, do they? They don't call it <LOCATION>Columbus World</LOCATION>,
do they? What about this guy <ORGANIZATION>Disney</ORGANIZATION>?;    Q: He was a great pioneer!;    A:
Yeah. He had a better agent than my guy. Took my land and my pizza. Tell me,
do they celebrate my birthday in the Indies?;    Q: In <LOCATION>America</LOCATION>, yes, they do,
but there is considerable protest over that now.;    A: Why, for God's sake?; 
  Q: They say you really didn't discover anything. There were tens of
thousands of Native Americans already there when you got there.;    A: Yeah,
but we got there! On three stinking little ships. With all sorts of rotten
sailors. And we didn't fall off the end of the world, either. I told them they
wouldn't. And now they say I didn't discover the place. Boy. That <LOCATION>America</LOCATION> is a
rip-off.;    Q: Would you like to apologize?;    A: To whom?;    Q: To the
Indians -- the Native Americans!;    A: Listen, maybe we can work a deal. I
could get a few of those acres in <LOCATION>Florida</LOCATION>, and I would give them a couple of
trinkets. Or beads. Those people loved beads in the old days!;    Q: They have
wised up.;    A: How about six pesos for <LOCATION>Manhattan Island</LOCATION>?;    Q: Somebody
already worked that deal. And now 2 1/2 million people live on <LOCATION>Manhattan
Island</LOCATION>!;    A: <PERSON>Holy Isabella</PERSON>. That many! Those Indians are everywhere. Tell me
something.;    Q: Yes.;    A: Could I maybe open a couple of pizza huts on
that island?;    Q: Too late, <LOCATION>Chris.</LOCATION>;    A: Yeah. Rip-off. How about
Chrisburgers?  </TEXT>
